reviews.text:
Ambiance: Fun & upbeat Mexican spot with a great patio! We loved sitting outside on a nice day and grabbing cocktails with appetizers. The sangrias were some of the best I've had in Houston and we loved the guacamole.

Quick service and kind servers. A bit on the pricey side, but delicious drinks & food! Limited parking available, street parking was the main option. Bar seating and regular tables available inside as well. Definitely would go back if in the area.

We came here 3 years ago and didn't have the best experience. Took a chance and came here for dinner last night. What a difference!

We were greeted within a minute of walking through the door & had water, chips, and salsa just a minute after being seated.

We ordered strawberry margs and beef faijitas (medium). Strawberry margs were very good. Lots of strawberry flavor and big strawberry garnish! Fajitas were a huge serving considering it ‚Äúserves 1-2‚Äù. Comes with all the fixings, tender, and piping hot.

Our server was amazing! She was always smiling and checked on us multiple times.

All-in-all we had a great experience and the food was solid! Recommend checking it out.

I was REALLY excited to go here because i follow them on Instagram and have been looking at the food and was like yummy!!  Pictures tell a whole another story. We ordered the Guacamole which is made to order, it's probably my most favorite thing with the thick chips. We had the Fajitas for two and added shrimp, well the shrimp/bacon was old and I could tell it was sitting for a while,  either that or they burnt it.
The Cilantro Rice was disappointing, beans tasted like they came from a can.  But, our waiter was great and the place is beautiful, really pretty.  Other than that, nothing exciting about this place, I felt let down but now we know not to go. The prices are okay, we paid about $180 for the two of us. Margaritas were awesome!! The dessert tray look good from far but up close it was not good, they should display fresh desserts every day, these looked like they had been sitting out for a few days, all soggy and melted, falling apart. Other than that, nothing else. Thanks but NO. Definitely need a redo on our Date Night !

The manager (some tall, bald guy in all black) accused my boyfriend and I of dining and dashing, despite my boyfriend using his card and receiving a notification the payment went through.

The manager chased both of us into the Red Dessert Dive, insulted us, and told us we deserve to have a terrible day because of the type of people we were.

Never mind we were the first and only patrons (at the moment) to frequent his business on the second day of this latest historic freeze (1/22/25 @ 11a), no one‚Äôs outside and along w/ these slick roads traveling from NRG to The Heights. We weren‚Äôt rude or difficult despite him bringing us syrup-less Sprite [that needed to be switched out] and subbed it for a can of 7Up. Bonus, the restaurant didn‚Äôt even have signage to indicate their place of business.

Unprofessional and out of line. 0/10

Always the best time here! Consistent, quality service and food. We usually get the queso, cheese enchiladas add fajita steak, street tacos, and coronarita.. we always ask for Fernanda, she‚Äôs the best! Great bar if sports are on, outdoor seating, secured parking.

editorial_summary.overview: An array of casual cantina-style Mexican food & American bar snacks in a sports bar & grill setting.

detailedReviews.text: I ate mole enchiladas. Wife had street tacos. Corn (elote) appetizer. Best chips and salsa in Houston. Great place to be. Very reasonable prices. Not Tex Mex. Not Mexican. Sort of a Mexican epicurean or fusion type of place. A little more Mex than Tex Mex...if you like all kinds of food (a Food Channel kind of person), you will love it. This is not your taco truck stuff. More like Mexico City or Wealthy Yucatan vibe...

detailedReviews.text: Fernanda was phenomenal. She was very nice and was the only server and bartender there on a Saturday afternoon. She took care of everything .I had the Pollo Con Marisco. It was great. The Mexican pizza is good too.

detailedReviews.author: Kimberly Truong
detailedReviews.text:
Can't say enough great things about Studewood Cantine. One of the best Mexican spots in Houston, and dare I say better than El Tiempo in my opinion. You can expect the food to be fresh and of the best quality, esp. when it comes to their beef fajitas. The chef and restaurant establishment as a whole know  how to serve both quality food and stellar customer service. Every time I dine or pick up, the wait staff and servers are consistently friendly, helpful and personable. Easily 5/5 stars.

Look no further for your Mexican fix, you'll be sure to get more than what you pay for, esp. when it comes to choices in the Heights area!

If you don‚Äôt like it, I love it! ;)

detailedReviews.author: Brian Dobbins
detailedReviews.text: Service was excellent, food was fantastic, and drinks were even better. I recommend the Cantine Black Barrel Margarita and the Pollo con Marisco - which was a large portion. Even had a great convo with the owner on review responses and customer service. We will definitely be back!

detailedReviews.author: Scott Pappas
detailedReviews.text:
Mexican food snob here‚Ä¶I was amazed at how good the food was! The chips were hot and fresh, salsa was nice and warm, beef fajita‚Äôs and carne asada were amazing (some of the best beef of any  Houston Mexican restaurant including Pappasito‚Äôs, El Tiempo and Lupe‚Äôs)! Grilled shrimp
Fajitas were super fresh and not served overcooked. Margaritas were great. Even had live music (great guitar player and singer). Definitely going back.

detailedReviews.author: James Anthony
detailedReviews.text:
1)  Jasmine and Fernanda are amazing servers that pay very close attention to the customers and their needs. Masters of their craft, please pay them more money!!
2)  The food is better than anywhere we have had in ages, and we eat mexican 2 to 3 times a week. This chef pays very close attention.
3)  The atmosphere is very relaxing, music is not too loud or too quiet. Comfy chairs, great lighting and the bar area is large an great for meeting new people.

In conclusion it is quite rare to find a place that has all 3 items listed above,  as connoiseurs we have searched and searched and never found one until now. What a wonderful facility. 100 / 100 Bravo! Please everyone go eat here so we can keep this place around!

detailedReviews.author: Tineshia Smith
detailedReviews.text: The atmosphere was laid back, the portion sizes were huge! Great tasting food and our waiter was everything. He was attentive, polite, went above and beyond to ensure that our order was corect

detailedReviews.author: Sara I
detailedReviews.text: Fresh flavors, ample space, unique interior and great service, thanks Fernanda.

detailedReviews.text: I frequent restaurants such as El Tiempo, Hugo‚Äôs, Carrabbas, A‚Äôbouzy etc and know the owners and waitstaff very well. I realize this is not on that level. But for goodness sakes I shouldn‚Äôt have to clean my sitting area, get my own utensils and napkins and tell the bartender how much my bill should be ! Subpar service on 3 different attempts. Go to I receive better service at the taquerias around the Heights!  I still left a tip but this was and has been a horrible service experience each and every time . It‚Äôs very sad because the food and the chef are great!

detailedReviews.author: Ruth Hernandez
detailedReviews.text:
I got here by mistake, our spot was closed and I just looked for happy hours nearby, I noticed that this place had thursday ALL DAY happy hour, Ive never been so happy for a Thursday before. We headed there around 4pm, it was pretty empty so the service was immediate.
We ordered some margaritas they brought us salsas and a basket of chips, and we ordered some of the special for happy hour.
I was surprised of how good and how big the portions were even for happy hour snacks/food, those margaritas were hitting perfectly, so we just ordered some more food and drinks, and the music was nice and good volume so we could talk and enjoy ourselves, definitely will add this place to my regular spots
++++++++++(try the asada tacos on corn tortilla)++++++++++++

detailedReviews.text: Great place, excellent service and amazing margaritas!!!

detailedReviews.author: Emily Pham
detailedReviews.text: Came a guest in a large party of 10! They were timely with service and the chips and salsa was good. The parking was confusing .. parked in a garage and probably wasn‚Äôt supposed to. But anyways the bathrooms were clean as well. I had the Mexican pizza and would recommend. It was sooooo good. Wish they had a huge sign with the restaurant name on the building. If the parking was easier I‚Äôd come here more often.

detailedReviews.author: Jess E
detailedReviews.text: Waited over an hour never received our food. Parking was limited. "Apparently a glitch in the system and the food was never entered". No options were given to correct the mistake. No apology given just a waste of our time. Poor customer service. Will probably never come here again.

detailedReviews.author: Bobby Arnold
detailedReviews.text: Had a conformed reservation for a party of 13 on 1/1/24. Arrived to a locked door & closed restaurant. Minimal expectation would have been a cancelation notice. Very poor way to do business

detailedReviews.author: Bob Cardenas
detailedReviews.text:
Excellent quesadillas and the El Sabroso plate are standouts, lamest service mars the experience time and again but I'll still come for the savor meals.

Went back, because the food is excellent and I'm pleased to report, sitting at the bar was the way to go (since I dines alone). The service was prompt and attentive without being a pain, thanks to bartender, James. I'll be back with family now that the weather is improving for outdoor seating.

UPDATE
Thank goodness this place has a consistent kitchen! I usually come here during off hours because it's deservedly popular. I dropped below 180lbs since mid summer, so this is my go to for off diet splurging.

LATEST UPDATE
Troubling issues yesterday. The anticipated order of beef quesadillas came without sour cream to counter the sliced jalapeno and the guacamole was stale and off putting. After mentioning it to the bartender, she came back with the news that the kitchen was out of sour cream and yes, the guacamole was bad. She was attentive at least, finally a professional.

One problem I've always had here is the vanishing wait or bar staff. Until she waited on me ( she is the upstairs manager pressed into bartending for an absentee), the staff seemed to have never worked in a restaurant before, long waits for tea refills, no queries about sweetener or not and the worst, not checking to see if I was ready to pay. They would walk around and never look over to see if I'm done or need anything at all.

DECEMBER 2023
The place was surprisingly festively decorated for Christmas, well done. The biggest improvement was the new ATTENTIVE bartender, no more waiting to order, waiting for refill inquiries and no more waiting for the bill to be presented. Plus, she was smiling often, no more dreary looking staff. As usual, the quesadillas were top shelf!

detailedReviews.author: A ‚ÄúAlly‚Äù Lopez
detailedReviews.text:
I was REALLY excited to go here because i follow them on Instagram and have been looking at the food and was like yummy!!  Pictures tell a whole another story. We ordered the Guacamole which is made to order, it's probably my most favorite thing with the thick chips. We had the Fajitas for two and added shrimp, well the shrimp/bacon was old and I could tell it was sitting for a while,  either that or they burnt it.
The Cilantro Rice was disappointing, beans tasted like they came from a can.  But, our waiter was great and the place is beautiful, really pretty.  Other than that, nothing exciting about this place, I felt let down but now we know not to go. The prices are okay, we paid about $180 for the two of us. Margaritas were awesome!! The dessert tray look good from far but up close it was not good, they should display fresh desserts every day, these looked like they had been sitting out for a few days, all soggy and melted, falling apart. Other than that, nothing else. Thanks but NO. Definitely need a redo on our Date Night !

detailedReviews.author: Chaco Ruiz
detailedReviews.text: We came here for a quick bite while we waited for our kids to be ready to be picked up nearby. We came in late afternoon/early evening and the place was almost empty. We chose where to sit, ordered our drinks and looked through the happy hour menu. We got two small plates, very good, and enjoyed a few drinks before we left. This was exactly what we were looking for. Great service and good food, can't beat that.

detailedReviews.author: Susan Austin
detailedReviews.text: We had a delightful group lunch here.

detailedReviews.author: Steve S.
detailedReviews.text: There are a plethora of options for Tex-Mex in Houston. In a crowded field, Studewood Cantine does nothing to stand out. I had a margarita and the steak fajitas. The margarita was ‚Äúspirit forward‚Äù, a plus, but overly sour.  When I switched to beer, the draft menu fleas fairly pedestrian and mostly comprised of large beer brands. Fajitas are my ‚Äúgo to‚Äù in Houston and these were passable, but there are at least 10+ places I‚Äôd rather go first. In the bright side, the live music was a nice touch.

detailedReviews.author: Ms Benz
detailedReviews.text:
I‚Äôve been to this location a handful of times and each time the service and staff is on point. There are plenty of TVs to watch the game around their restaurant. I don‚Äôt recommend sitting in the back door the restroom because it smells bad back there. The last time we went, we got stuck in the back and it was not as enjoyable.
The food is always great, and the portions are large. The parking is kind of dicey. There is a parking lot across the street but sometimes it‚Äôs full and you have to find street parking down the street.

detailedReviews.author: Oscar Gonzalez
detailedReviews.text:
First time here , crowd was light made my lunch more enjoyable since I only had an hour lunch break.. Sat at Bar for lunch Bartender Eric was an Excellent Host  ,Bartender and Server...  Great Lunch
Definitely will be back !!!

detailedReviews.author: Inez Garzia
detailedReviews.text: Great food,  great drinks.

detailedReviews.author: Ryan Hood
detailedReviews.text: I was pleasantly surprised by this place. I expected run of the mill tex mex and got some great examples instead. The salsas were great, the red sauce being one of the best I've had. The original queso was wonderful better than most options out there. All of our entrees were good and I look forward to trying the pozole on the weekend. The service was a bit slow or non existent at times on a slow Thursday night. I only got a water refill once. But I will definitely return.

detailedReviews.author: Crystal
detailedReviews.text:
Place was easy to find with convenient parking. They offer happy hour on Saturdays.
The queso flamedo with chorizo is really good. Bar tacos de carne asada is also really good. Their flour tortillas are the best.
Drinks are not too strong. You can have a couple and still be coherent.

Their restroom doors are weird.
Instead of push / pull .. it‚Äôs pull / push..
also when you got or open the door.. the handle is on the opposite side

When you question the door situation.. the waitress agrees with you and brings you water ü•πü•π

detailedReviews.author: Kyle Brown
detailedReviews.text: If you‚Äôre looking for great margaritas, great fajitas, and a manager that cares about your experience - this is the Mexican food restaurant for you.

detailedReviews.author: David & Jenny Weekley
detailedReviews.text: I enjoyed the beef tacos from here at a pop up taco stand at the car wash on Ella! The owner was promoting the restaurant and giving out free tacos. So clever! Really delicious tacos! Looking forward to trying out the restaurant.

detailedReviews.author: G B
detailedReviews.text: We brought our 8O+ year old in-laws for an early dinner and our waitress couldn‚Äôt have been more gracious. My Campechana Avocado was delicious. The only complaint was that the brisket taco was a little dry but otherwise everything was great. I highly recommend and will be returning!

detailedReviews.author: Megan M
detailedReviews.text: Great place for groups. We were able to do individual checks. The pineapple jalapeno marg was top notch.

detailedReviews.author: Rodney D.
detailedReviews.text: Had the Beef Quesadillas, Beef street tacos & nachos!  The service was just Ok... appears they were short of people so it made for a long eve!  The food was less than Ok... the Fajita Beef wasn't tender and was tough.  Nice to try something new, but will stay with the other Mexican restaurants.

detailedReviews.author: Eddie Gamez
detailedReviews.text: Campechana!!

detailedReviews.author: Hamza Haroon
detailedReviews.text: Amazing fajitas. Amazing customer service. Great drinks. Low noise.

detailedReviews.author: S. P
detailedReviews.text: First time here. I had the grilled vegetable tacos with a side of black beans and spicy rice.  The tortillas chips were not too greasy and sauces were exceptional! The young lady waiting on us was attentive. And the atmosphere is nice. I'll be back.

detailedReviews.author: Diana T
detailedReviews.text: First time here and our server David L was SO helpful and so nice. Very knowledgeable not only of the menu but of the area which was cool. The margarita was amazing and such a good price and the food was well seasoned but not overly salty like other places. It tasted more homemade than most. Will be coming back!

detailedReviews.author: Charly Perez
detailedReviews.text:
Incredible incredible food! Staff is amazing! Location and place are unbelievable! Patio is just WOW! The vibes are wonderful
You can watch all kinds of games and my favorite of all..... they carry tequila La Santa, I could not ask for more in one place  over all 10

detailedReviews.author: Neel Shah
detailedReviews.text: Amazing food and people

detailedReviews.author: Teila Adams
detailedReviews.text: Love their happy hour. The food is always delicious. My husband and I visit at least one a week.

detailedReviews.author: E Wyatt
detailedReviews.text: Love the atmosphere; immaculate; roomy ; food was delicious üòã . Will surely visit again and tell others to visit.

detailedReviews.author: Jeff Teetz
detailedReviews.text: $2 Taco Tuesday. Great Tacos

detailedReviews.author: TheWHworth
detailedReviews.text: Food was really good, felt very welcomed as soon as we came in. Good service. Will definitely come back!!

detailedReviews.author: Elizabeth Villarreal
detailedReviews.text: Came across this restaurant by driving near it and we decided to check it out. It did not disappoint! Food was really good, it‚Äôs hard to find good Mexican food spots, but this place will be on my top list. üòã

detailedReviews.author: April H
detailedReviews.text:
First, David (server) = 5 ‚≠êÔ∏è! He was very helpful and friendly!
Food = 4‚≠êÔ∏è
Happy hour and the manager = 0‚≠êÔ∏è
Thursday is advertised as All Day Happy Hour. So $5 for a cheap 10oz beer, and $5 for a yellow margarita, that is nothing but sweet and sour. Equally sour, is the manager. üòí Save your money on an $8 HH quesadilla because you can get three times the size for $17-20 (size of three HH ones).
To the GM - we see what you‚Äôre doing to make money - not cool. Step it up, and be better to your employees!
David, keep up the great work!

detailedReviews.author: Kendra Nettles
detailedReviews.text: Our waiter (David) was AMAZING! Though, happy hour was pretty disappointing, the margaritas were too sweet and the portion sizes were small. Also, the manger made me feel uncomfortable and needs to work on his social skills, but we love you David! Hope you find a new restaurant to work at so we can come visit you.

detailedReviews.author: Keriana Sanders
detailedReviews.text:
David is an awesome waiter and made us feel so welcome, he gave us great service and was so friendly and helped us navigate the menu. The green sauce was awesome.

But I must warn y‚Äôall, the margaritas are green AF which everyone in Texas knows that means it‚Äôs *ALL* sweet n sour. Margs should be white or light translucent green. Also the happy hour is very limited and not a great deal. Finally the manager rubbed us the wrong way. He was micro managing our waiter and made everyone at the table feel uncomfortable, not a friendly dude.

David, the five stars are for you! Thanks for the awesome service!

positive.author: Alejandro Sandz
positive.text: Fantastic food.  Try the pozole on Fridays and Saturdays.  The Mexican Bowl is badass.  The service is GReat, very friendly.   The fajita nachos are super good.

positive.author: MeetWithMacey
positive.text:
Ambiance: Fun & upbeat Mexican spot with a great patio! We loved sitting outside on a nice day and grabbing cocktails with appetizers. The sangrias were some of the best I've had in Houston and we loved the guacamole.

Quick service and kind servers. A bit on the pricey side, but delicious drinks & food! Limited parking available, street parking was the main option. Bar seating and regular tables available inside as well. Definitely would go back if in the area.

neutral.author: Bob Cardenas
neutral.text:
Excellent quesadillas and the El Sabroso plate are standouts, lamest service mars the experience time and again but I'll still come for the savor meals.

Went back, because the food is excellent and I'm pleased to report, sitting at the bar was the way to go (since I dines alone). The service was prompt and attentive without being a pain, thanks to bartender, James. I'll be back with family now that the weather is improving for outdoor seating.

UPDATE
Thank goodness this place has a consistent kitchen! I usually come here during off hours because it's deservedly popular. I dropped below 180lbs since mid summer, so this is my go to for off diet splurging.

LATEST UPDATE
Troubling issues yesterday. The anticipated order of beef quesadillas came without sour cream to counter the sliced jalapeno and the guacamole was stale and off putting. After mentioning it to the bartender, she came back with the news that the kitchen was out of sour cream and yes, the guacamole was bad. She was attentive at least, finally a professional.

One problem I've always had here is the vanishing wait or bar staff. Until she waited on me ( she is the upstairs manager pressed into bartending for an absentee), the staff seemed to have never worked in a restaurant before, long waits for tea refills, no queries about sweetener or not and the worst, not checking to see if I was ready to pay. They would walk around and never look over to see if I'm done or need anything at all.

DECEMBER 2023
The place was surprisingly festively decorated for Christmas, well done. The biggest improvement was the new ATTENTIVE bartender, no more waiting to order, waiting for refill inquiries and no more waiting for the bill to be presented. Plus, she was smiling often, no more dreary looking staff. As usual, the quesadillas were top shelf!
